* ============================================================
*  NAV DELETED-RECORD SMOKE TEST  (self-contained, throwaway table)
*
*  Status:  CANDIDATE / REVIEW_BEFORE_EXECUTION.
*  Safety:  MUTATING, but only on a throwaway table (NAVDELTMP) that is ERASEd
*           at the end. Does NOT touch the pinocchio (or any other) fixtures.
*  Purpose: Document how ordered navigation behaves with SET DELETED ON and a
*           deleted record sitting at an endpoint / in the middle of the order.
*
*  WHY A THROWAWAY TABLE
*  ---------------------
*  DELETE on a CDX table marks the DBF record and best-effort updates the LMDB
*  index; RECALL may not fully restore the index entry. To avoid leaving the big
*  fixtures' index out of sync with their DBF, this test builds its own tiny
*  table, mutates that, and erases it.
*
*  WHAT TO OBSERVE
*  ---------------
*  Rows are inserted OUT OF SID ORDER so index order differs from record order:
*    recno 1..6  =  SID 30,10,50,20,60,40
*    SID order   =  10(r2) 20(r4) 30(r1) 40(r6) 50(r3) 60(r5)
*  So an ordered TOP must land on recno 2 (SID 10), proving index order.
*  The deleted sections then show whether TOP/SKIP under SET DELETED ON skip a
*  deleted record or land on it -- read the "Recno:" (TALK) lines and DISPLAY.
*
*  RUN
*  ---
*  DOTSCRIPT TRACE scripts\pinocchio\nav_deleted_smoke.dts OUT tmp\pinocchio\deleted_smoke.log
* ============================================================
SET ECHO OFF
SET TIMER ON
SET TALK ON

* Use the default roots (guaranteed to exist); the table is temporary.
ECHO === G0. build throwaway x64 table NAVDELTMP, indexed by SID ===
CREATE X64 NAVDELTMP (SID N(8), LNAME C(20))

* NOTE: bare APPEND (no args) appends one blank record and positions on it;
* "APPEND BLANK" is only a compatibility spelling and is not implemented here.
APPEND
REPLACE SID WITH "30"
REPLACE LNAME WITH "Thirty"
APPEND
REPLACE SID WITH "10"
REPLACE LNAME WITH "Ten"
APPEND
REPLACE SID WITH "50"
REPLACE LNAME WITH "Fifty"
APPEND
REPLACE SID WITH "20"
REPLACE LNAME WITH "Twenty"
APPEND
REPLACE SID WITH "60"
REPLACE LNAME WITH "Sixty"
APPEND
REPLACE SID WITH "40"
REPLACE LNAME WITH "Forty"

COUNT
CDX CREATE
CDX ADDTAG SID
BUILDLMDB CLEAN YES
CDX TAGS

SET INDEX TO NAVDELTMP
SET ORDER TO TAG SID

ECHO === G1. baseline ordered walk (no deletes): expect recno 2,4,1,6,3,5 ===
TOP
DISPLAY
SKIP
SKIP
SKIP
SKIP
SKIP
BOTTOM
DISPLAY

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* G2. deleted record AT THE TOP endpoint, unfiltered, SET DELETED ON
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO === G2. delete SID 10 (recno 2, the ordered TOP), then SET DELETED ON ===
GO 2
DELETE
SET DELETED ON
ECHO --- G2a. TOP: skips deleted SID 10 -> recno 4 (SID 20), or lands recno 2 if RawOrder ignores DELETED ---
TOP
DISPLAY
ECHO --- restore ---
SET DELETED OFF
GO 2
RECALL

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* G3. deleted record in the MIDDLE of the order, unfiltered SKIP
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO === G3. delete SID 30 (recno 1, the 3rd in SID order), SET DELETED ON ===
GO 1
DELETE
SET DELETED ON
ECHO --- G3a. TOP=SID10(r2); SKIP->SID20(r4); SKIP-> SID40(r6) if deleted SID30 skipped, else SID30(r1) ---
TOP
SKIP
DISPLAY
SKIP
DISPLAY
ECHO --- restore ---
SET DELETED OFF
GO 1
RECALL

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* G4. deleted record honored under an ACTIVE FILTER (LogicalView path)
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO === G4. filter to a 2-row set, delete the first, confirm filtered TOP moves ===
SET FILTER TO LNAME = "Ten"
COUNT
TOP
DISPLAY
DELETE
SET FILTER TO
SET FILTER TO LNAME = "Ten"
SET DELETED ON
ECHO --- G4a. filtered TOP with the only match deleted -> no visible row (nav reports end) ---
TOP
ECHO --- restore ---
SET DELETED OFF
SET FILTER TO
RECALL ALL

* ------------------------------------------------------------
* Cleanup: drop the throwaway table.
* ------------------------------------------------------------
ECHO === G5. cleanup: ERASE the throwaway table ===
CLOSE
ERASE TABLE NAVDELTMP CONFIRM

ECHO ============================================================
ECHO DELETED-RECORD SMOKE COMPLETE. Record for each section whether a deleted
ECHO record was SKIPPED or LANDED ON:
ECHO   G2 (unfiltered TOP, deleted endpoint): recno 4 = skipped; recno 2 = landed.
ECHO   G3 (unfiltered SKIP, deleted middle) : SID 40 = skipped; SID 30 = landed.
ECHO   G4 (filtered TOP, only match deleted) : "at end" = correctly hidden.
ECHO These document the SET DELETED semantics for ordered CDX navigation so the
ECHO behavior is intentional rather than incidental. If G2/G3 LAND ON the deleted
ECHO record, that is the RawOrder-does-not-consult-DELETED path and is the next
ECHO thing to decide on (route unfiltered nav through the visibility gate too).
ECHO ============================================================
